history.content: I don't think wanting to work 20 hrs will lower your chances at 8 (I've put 20 before and gotten an 8hr position). Professors would probably prefer to hire 8 hrs who want to work more anyway (not necessarily because they'll make you do more than 8 hours of work but because it shows a level of commitment to teaching).

On the TA application, I need to answer: "How many hours per week do you want to work?"

TA's are hired as either 8 or 20 hour TAs. 

If I put 20 hours as my answer to the question, does that lower my chances of being selected as an 8 hour TA?

I am happy to work more than 8 hours a week even if I am hired as an 8 hour TA. In addition, indicating that I want to work more than 8 hours looks better. However, I'm afraid that it lowers the chance im hired if the application system has some weird design that changes the priority of applications that have non-8 hour entries to this question for placement in 8 hour TA roles. Does the application system do this?
